-- BNY Mellon Earnings Triple as Stock Rebound Boosts Asset-Management Fees
-- JoAnne Norton
-- 2010-07-20T10:33:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/bny-mellon-posts-second-quarter-eps-on-continuing-operations-of-55-cents.html

          
          
             Bank of New York Mellon Corp., the
world’s biggest custody bank, had second-quarter profit from
continuing operations of 55 cents a share. Analysts surveyed by
Bloomberg had estimated profit of 55 cents on average. It
couldn’t immediately be determined if the numbers are
comparable.  
          
          


  


        